Dialog.text: Commander Dahl. This is Kaspar. Status report.
All major servers and terminals are locked down. Rip and Intecept Protocols are in operation.
Searching access patterns within the last three hours. Progress estimate. Sixty three percent.
Affirmative. Resuming.
Commander Dahl. This is Kaspar. Morgan Yu sighted. I repeat Morgan Yu sighted.
Commander Dahl, do you copy? Commander Dahl...?
Server Arx F30 through F37 ripped.
Index cluster. Null mask reference. Deleted.
Ghost job InterceptD operational. Sensitives routing to shuttle cache.
(Machine Sounds)
Dialog.notes: Variant 1. Something like a hard drive defragging. Low tone machine language boops.

Dialog.text: Servers Arx F13 through F21 ripped.
Psychotronics data. Priority tag. Delivery node Occam LSDS-3.
Data vault DVM-3. Prior ejection.
I read you.
Holding. Small group of survivors still present.
Network is still locked down. Alex has no means of access.
Installing Rip and Intercept protocols. Thirty five percent complete.
Negative. The encryption is trivial, but another user is employing countermeasures against me.
I would like dedicate more processing power to it.
There is no person aboard Talos I who can perform operations as fast-
Improbable. There are none like me.
Oxygen nearly depleted. I expect loss of consciousness momentarily.
Killphrase. Navarre, Orange, Delilah.
